data: The Seabeast is out there somewhere. And so is safety. Go find one of them. But before you depart, choose your first mate.
Your first mate settles in and asks where to next.

You get a bad feeling. You scan the surrounding waters for the tell tale dark shadows just below the surface that preempt an attack from the depths. But this time the source for concern isn't from below the water but speeding just above it. Four armed men are quickly approaching straight towards your boat. YOUR boat! It's not looking good. These men are definitely pirates.

The radio buzzes to life.  The voice of a middle aged man. A documentary producer who explains that the crew for his hit show "Shark Chasers" is stranded on a small, tide reliant island off the coast while they were shooting an episode of his hit show. He begs you to rescue the crew of his hit show before high tide returns and erases the island, and in turn, his hit show.

You come upon a dingy in the open sea. Miraculously, there is still a man alive on theraft. But there are also signs that there may have been a struggle on board. Scraps ofbright colored clothing that don’t match the man’s clothes and dried blood on asecond life jacket. You ask the man if there was anyone with him and he says no oneelse survived when their ship sunk.

You receive a distress call from the Nautilus, captained by one of your bitter rivals, Captain Pratt. The contents of the message are unclear, but you do manage to extract a set of coordinates from the crackling broadcast
Uh oh ... the pirates are back! This time on jet skis!
Hmm ... this looks like it could be a good fishing spot. Want to sit a spell and see what we can catch?
Medical supplies are floating in the water.
Cristo ... what a kid? Seriously? Desperate times.
Try to outrun them. It doesn't look hopeful but it may be your only chance
Decline. You’re not a fan of the show.
Jet skis can’t be an effective transport for pirates. Voice your concern to them.
Let's grab them and try not to think about what has recently taken place here.
Viktoria ... hmm big gap in work history. Skilled with a knife?
Fight. The pirates will learn to regret their life choices
Agree, but only after you've made sure the Seabeast isn't in the area.
Give him food and water, but ask that he stay on his raft and tow him to the nearest port.
Ask them to rate their distress on a scale from 1 to 10, 10 being the most distressed, 1 being the least distressed
It's the ocean's now. Let's move on.
Agree to drop everything and head out there.
Cut him loose and pray that no one else finds him before the sea swallows him whole.
Suspend all duties and head to the coordiantes
Ask [FM] if they've heard of Shark Chasers.
Watch a few episodes of Shark Chasers before deciding what to do.
